Actually, `textureLoader = new THREE.TextureLoader()` runs synchronously first, then the IIFE is created. So by the time `initScene()` runs, `textureLoader` should be defined.

Hmm, but wait - `THREE.TextureLoader` requires `THREE` to be loaded. If THREE hasn't loaded yet when this line runs, it would fail. But the Three.js script is loaded via the metadata.scripts, so it should be available.

